         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Cambewarra, Shoalhaven, New South Wales, ¶ Feb. 8th 1890. ¶ Honoured Sir, ¶  ¶ I take the liberty of forwarding you a small parcel containing the leaves, fruit and bark of a tree that is very scarce h...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.02.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Weir</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M45, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Answ 14/2/90'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Cambewarra, Shoalhaven, New South Wales,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Feb. 8th 1890.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Honoured Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take the liberty of forwarding you a small parcel containing the leaves, fruit and bark of a tree that is very scarce here. This tree does not produce fruit very often; I have been watching for it ever since I became acquainted with Mr Baurlen;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bäuerlen.</p>
               </note> the tree is not know<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">known?</p>
               </note> by him. I have had better specimens of the bark in my possession than those I now send you; the largest specimen, I have had for years beside me; the small one was gathered yesterday. I have manufactured some fair specimens of corks from the bark, with an old razor blade; when it can be had large enough it makes very good floats for fishing nets.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Accept my best thanks for the copy of your work on "Select Extra-Tropical Plants."<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Presumably B88.12.01.</p>
               </note> I have read it twice over — it is one of the most <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">readable</hi>
               </seg> books I ever perused. When the present ignorant money-grubling generation have dissolved into their primitive mud, and a more enlightened race inhabits Australia, your works will come to the front — and remain there.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose a cutting<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Cutting not found.</p>
               </note> by the Rev. David Landsborough, of Kilmarnock Scotland, they seem to be doing their best to naturalise the eucalypts in Scotland.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thomas Weir.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Baron Von Mueller.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
